Event: A thursday. Is that REALLY necessary  ? Have u ever heard of school and horrible mums
Post: "Another Thursday, another day of struggling to keep up with my classes while juggling the responsibilities of being a mom. It's like, I get it, being a mom is hard, but can't my teachers just cut me some slack? Do they not understand that I have a child to raise too? But no, instead, they pile on the homework and expect me to be in class bright and early every day. And don't even get me started on my own mom, who seems to think that my sole purpose in life is to be her personal errand girl. Like, hello, I have my own life to live too, you know? But nope, she just keeps piling on the pressure, expecting me to do everything for her while I'm trying to pursue my own dreams and goals. It's like, can't they just see that I'm doing my best here? That maybe, just maybe, I'm not superhuman and can't handle everything all at once? But nope, they just keep pushing me, pushing me, pushing me... until I feel like I'm about to break. And then, when I do finally break, they'll be the first ones to judge me for it. Like, seriously, can't they just give a girl a break? #overwhelmed #momlife #studentlife"
